  "response": "To watch the first Fox News/Facebook 2016 Republican primary debate after it's over, you have several options:\n\n1. **Fox News Website**: Check Fox News' official website, where they often provide video replays of major events and debates.\n   \n2. **Facebook**: Given that Facebook partnered with Fox News for this debate, they might have hosted videos or clips of the debate on their official pages or event pages.\n\n3. **YouTube**: Search for the debate on YouTube. Many broadcasters and users typically upload full-length debates or highlights soon after they air.\n   \n4. **News Outlets' Websites**: Major news websites like CNN, MSNBC, or other political news-focused websites might have coverage and video clips available.\n\n5. **Streaming Services**: Subscription-based services like Hulu, Sling TV, or others sometimes have news broadcasts available for replay.\n\nMake sure to use specific search terms like \"Fox News Facebook Republican primary debate 2016 full video\" to help find what you're looking for.",
